<article class="styleguide-content">
    <p id="intro">This is <a href="https://www.github.com/dosomething/neue">Neue</a>, our interface framework and pattern library. It defines a set of base styles and common patterns shared throughout our website. It's a strong foundation for building beautiful interfaces.</p>

    <p>Neue was built for our internal needs at DoSomething.org, but it could also work for your organization. Feel free to fork our <a href="https://github.com/dosomething/neue">GitHub repository</a> and use it as a starting point for your own pattern library, or read more about why we <a href="https://blog.dosomething.org/we-open-sourced-our-code-heres-why-you-should-too/">open-source our code</a>.</p>

    <h2 id="base">Base Styles</h2>
    <p>Content is the basis for our design, so we need a strong typographic foundation. We define base HTML classes with comfortable font-size and spacing for readability, and a clear information hierarchy between elements.</p>

